column8: A hundred people with disabilities will get their refunds from JJPTR.The financial scheme’s 28-year-old founder Johnson Lee is expected to personally hand the money back to them on Tuesday, said Gerakan Youth deputy chief Andy Yong Kim Seng.“It has taken several weeks to get in touch with the top management of the scheme. I’m glad Lee has agreed to return the money to this group,” he said here.Yong, who is also the Gerakan legal bureau deputy chairman, said about 20 people from Segambut and Kepong had approached the Gerakan service centres for help.http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2017..._medium=twitter
